e revenue per line. \n*   **Relation to Total Connectivity Revenue:** Service Lines (via Starlink Subscribers) are the primary driver of consumer revenue, which represented "over 60% of Connectivity segment revenue" in 2025. However, because total Connectivity revenue also includes enterprise, government, and Starlink Mobile revenues (which are not counted as Starlink Subscriber Service Lines), the Service Line count only reflects the consumer/personal subscription portion of the total Connectivity segment revenue, not the entirety of it. Furthermore, the text notes that revenue could be even higher than the Service Line count suggests because "multiple people may share a single Service Line, including within a household," meaning the actual number of paying end users is "meaningfully higher" than the Service Line count.',
